<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="441" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,1743,2022]" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Iredale &amp; Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[151,394,1743,1769]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="opiparus">
<emphasis box="[151,394,1743,1769]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">Leptochiton opiparus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="(M. Sars MS, Loven, 1846)" baseAuthorityName="M. Sars MS, Loven" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[729,1182,1743,1770]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alveolus">
<emphasis box="[729,853,1743,1769]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">L. alveolus</emphasis>
(M. Sars MS, 
<bibRefCitation author="Loven, S. L." box="[1028,1173,1743,1770]" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" pagination="134 - 160" refId="ref18435" refString="Loven, S. L. (1846) Index molluscorum litora Scandinaviae Occidentalia habitantium. Ofverssigt Af Kungel Svenska Vetenskaps- Akademiens Forhandlinger, 3, 134 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59081" type="journal article" year="1846">Lovén, 1846</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A." pageId="40" pageNumber="441" refId="ref18267" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1985) Monograph of living chitons. 1. E. J. Brill / W. Backhuys, Leiden, 240 pp." type="book" year="1985">Kaas &amp; Van Belle (1985)</bibRefCitation>
and later with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[391,516,1779,1805]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[391,516,1779,1805]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A." box="[557,840,1779,1806]" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" refId="ref18304" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1987) Monograph of living chitons. 3. E. J. Brill / W. Backhuys, Leiden, 302 pp." type="book" year="1987">Kaas &amp; Van Belle (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. In my opinion some of the species that were synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[285,412,1815,1841]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[285,412,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are valid. Typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[625,751,1815,1841]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[625,751,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits the Pacific Ocean from off the Pacific side of Hokkaido (
<geoCoordinate box="[229,329,1852,1878]" degrees="40" direction="north" minutes="12" orientation="latitude" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" precision="925" value="40.2">40°12’N</geoCoordinate>
), the Sea of Okhotsk and the Bering Sea and North and South America’s Pacific waters southwards to 
<geoCoordinate box="[181,275,1888,1914]" degrees="42" direction="south" minutes="40" orientation="latitude" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" precision="925" value="-42.666668">42°40’S</geoCoordinate>
, at depth of 
<quantity box="[416,580,1888,1914]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9119999999999997" metricValueMax="3.7239999999999993" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" unit="m" value="1912.0" valueMax="3724.0" valueMin="100.0">100 to 3724 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko, B. I. &amp; Sellanes, J." box="[595,883,1887,1914]" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" pagination="259 - 279" refId="ref19195" refString="Sirenko, B. I. &amp; Sellanes, J. (2016) Update of the genus Leptochiton (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) in Chilean deep waters: three new reports and description of two new species. Zootaxa, 4173 (3), 259 - 279. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4173.3.5" type="journal article" year="2016">Sirenko &amp; Sellanes 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In the Western Pacific, further south from Hokkaido to 
<collectingCountry box="[250,403,1923,1950]" name="New Zealand" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, more than 10 species which belong to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[887,1012,1923,1949]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[887,1012,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group are living. Therefore I think 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Iredale &amp; Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1925" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="opiparus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">L. opiparus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid species. It cannot be excluded that 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nierstrasz, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[754,1165,1959,1986]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rissoi">
<emphasis box="[754,956,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">Leptochiton rissoi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nierstrasz, H. F." box="[971,1157,1959,1986]" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref18698" refString="Nierstrasz, H. F. (1905) Die Chitonen der Siboga-Expedition. Siboga Expeditie, 48, 1 - 112, pls. 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1905">Nierstrasz, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwabe, E. &amp; Sellanes, J." pageId="40" pageNumber="441" pagination="31 - 55" refId="ref18862" refString="Schwabe, E. &amp; Sellanes, J. (2010) Revision of Chilean bathyal chitons Mollusca: Polyplacophora) associated with cold-seeps, including description of a new species of Leptochiton (Leptochitonidae). Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution, 10 (1), 31 - 55. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13127 - 009 - 0002 - 6" type="journal article" year="2010">Schwabe &amp; Sellanes (2010)</bibRefCitation>
to be present in SW Australian waters represents 
<emphasis box="[883,1131,1995,2021]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="441">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Iredale &amp; Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[883,1127,1995,2021]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="40" pageNumber="441" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="opiparus">Leptochiton opiparus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
